782
00:33:49.790 --> 00:33:50.980
And when you
choked the life out

783
00:33:51.020 --> 00:33:53.490
of her on her 30th birthday.
- Objection.

784
00:33:53.530 --> 00:33:54.830
Sustained.

785
00:33:56.960 --> 00:33:59.230
Nothing further.

786
00:34:08.780 --> 00:34:10.140
Hey.

787
00:34:10.240 --> 00:34:11.700
Hey.

788
00:34:11.840 --> 00:34:13.250
The jury isn't buying
into this whole

789
00:34:13.310 --> 00:34:15.020
Cash White nonsense. right?

790
00:34:15.080 --> 00:34:17.020
I mean. I despise the man.
but he didn't kill her.

791
00:34:17.080 --> 00:34:19.690
We are doing our best
to make that clear. Lucas.

792
00:34:19.820 --> 00:34:22.720
And I think the jury
knows that. too.

793
00:34:23.860 --> 00:34:26.810
OK.
Thank you.

794
00:34:30.060 --> 00:34:31.830
Really believe that?

795
00:34:31.870 --> 00:34:35.640
At best. the jury hates him
as a human being.

796
00:34:35.670 --> 00:34:39.000
At worst. no.
they actually think he did it.

797
00:34:39.060 --> 00:34:43.140
which means
we need to rehabilitate him.

798
00:34:43.210 --> 00:34:44.170
How?

799
00:34:44.240 --> 00:34:45.910
I don't know.

800
00:34:45.980 --> 00:34:50.080
But even a horrible
human being

801
00:34:50.180 --> 00:34:54.710
like Cash does something
decent once in a while.

802
00:34:54.750 --> 00:34:57.690
Oh. wouldn't bet on it.

803
00:34:57.790 --> 00:35:00.730
Well.
we have nothing to lose.

804
00:35:04.700 --> 00:35:08.000
Cash is just as selfish
and horrible as we'd imagined.

805
00:35:08.070 --> 00:35:10.700
No public service.
Doesn't help out his mother.

806
00:35:10.770 --> 00:35:12.110
He give to charity?

807
00:35:12.210 --> 00:35:13.220
Next to nothing.

808
00:35:13.260 --> 00:35:15.210
on a gross income
of $12 million.

809
00:35:15.240 --> 00:35:17.210
Well. that was
a total waste of time.

810
00:35:17.240 --> 00:35:18.550
Well. not exactly.

811
00:35:18.650 --> 00:35:20.310
Cash told me what
really happened the day

812
00:35:20.380 --> 00:35:22.050
he was arrested for assault.

813
00:35:22.150 --> 00:35:23.420
What really happened?

814
00:35:23.450 --> 00:35:26.290
Angela was supposed
to be babysitting

815
00:35:26.420 --> 00:35:27.990
his infant daughter.

816
00:35:28.050 --> 00:35:29.890
but went on
a coke bender instead.

817
00:35:29.920 --> 00:35:32.590
Cash got home.
found the baby alone.

818
00:35:32.660 --> 00:35:35.030
crying. covered in feces.

819
00:35:35.060 --> 00:35:36.800
Why didn't he tell you
this before?

820
00:35:36.900 --> 00:35:39.400
Because he didn't want
to tarnish her legacy.

821
00:35:39.470 --> 00:35:42.400
He felt he owed it to her.
given how badly he treated her.

822
00:35:42.440 --> 00:35:44.340
How do you know
he's not just making this up?

823
00:35:44.400 --> 00:35:45.740
He has lots of evidence--

824
00:35:45.810 --> 00:35:48.070
surveillance video
inside and outside the house.

825
00:35:48.170 --> 00:35:50.480
This is why Angela
asked the DA's office

826
00:35:50.610 --> 00:35:51.760
to drop the charges.

827
00:35:51.800 --> 00:35:53.780
At a minimum.
it'll provide some context

828
00:35:53.850 --> 00:35:55.180
for his violent outburst.

829
00:35:55.250 --> 00:35:57.820
Yeah. if we introduce it.

830
00:35:57.880 --> 00:35:59.620
If?

831
00:35:59.650 --> 00:36:01.050
I don't know. Nick.

832
00:36:01.120 --> 00:36:04.270
The idea of blaming Angela
for her own assault

833
00:36:04.310 --> 00:36:06.790
feels disgusting.

834
00:36:06.890 --> 00:36:08.430
Not to mention her legacy.

835
00:36:08.500 --> 00:36:10.260
Like. her husband doesn't
need to know all of this.

836
00:36:10.360 --> 00:36:12.160
not at this point.
It doesn't feel right.

837
00:36:12.290 --> 00:36:13.830
Of course it doesn't.
but that's not the point.

838
00:36:13.930 --> 00:36:16.140
As distasteful
as this might sound.

839
00:36:16.270 --> 00:36:18.460
there is a distinction.
if not a difference.

840
00:36:18.490 --> 00:36:19.640
between a man flipping out

841
00:36:19.740 --> 00:36:21.470
after someone
endangers his baby

842
00:36:21.570 --> 00:36:23.470
and a man flipping out
over something insignificant.

843
00:36:23.500 --> 00:36:24.640
It's like
the difference between

844
00:36:24.680 --> 00:36:26.250
murder and manslaughter.

845
00:36:26.310 --> 00:36:27.810
They're both horrible crimes.

846
00:36:27.850 --> 00:36:29.850
but one is clearly worse
than the other.

847
00:36:29.980 --> 00:36:33.350
I get it intellectually.
but. well.

848
00:36:33.450 --> 00:36:36.310
the idea of trying to parse
domestic violence

849
00:36:36.350 --> 00:36:37.640
makes me uncomfortable.

850
00:36:37.670 --> 00:36:39.820
You know what makes me
uncomfortable. Sam?

851
00:36:39.850 --> 00:36:42.810
The defendant walking free
and killing another woman

852
00:36:42.850 --> 00:36:44.560
or staring down her husband.
Lucas Peters.

853
00:36:44.630 --> 00:36:46.700
and telling him
we should have done better.

854
00:36:46.800 --> 00:36:49.660
Alan Ross needs to spend
the rest of his life in prison.

855
00:36:49.690 --> 00:36:53.070
And if the cost of doing
that makes us uncomfortable.

856
00:36:53.140 --> 00:36:54.540
so be it.

857
00:37:04.950 --> 00:37:06.050
Hey.

858
00:37:08.650 --> 00:37:11.890
Look. I know Nick thinks
it's a good idea. but--

859
00:37:12.030 --> 00:37:14.830
Well. if it helps our case.

860
00:37:14.930 --> 00:37:17.020
But does it?

861
00:37:17.060 --> 00:37:19.600
We've already established that
Cash didn't commit the murder.

862
00:37:19.670 --> 00:37:21.670
Even better.
we've established that

863
00:37:21.740 --> 00:37:23.370
he couldn't have committed
the murder.

864
00:37:23.400 --> 00:37:24.700
That should be enough.

865
00:37:24.730 --> 00:37:27.610
Yeah. but Cash is
a hell of a target.

866
00:37:27.670 --> 00:37:30.340
He's easy to hate.

867
00:37:30.400 --> 00:37:31.900
easy to blame.

868
00:37:32.730 --> 00:37:35.580
Yeah. but trying to
somehow rationalize

869
00:37:35.680 --> 00:37:38.920
his horrific behavior.
well. it could backfire.

870
00:37:39.020 --> 00:37:40.590
alienate the jury even more.

871
00:37:40.690 --> 00:37:42.420
Yeah. it's possible. but--

872
00:37:42.560 --> 00:37:46.710
It is never OK to beat the
hell out of your girlfriend.

873
00:37:49.900 --> 00:37:53.070
Full stop.

874
00:38:00.230 --> 00:38:04.540
Where were you on the night
of the murder at 12:19 a.m.?

875
00:38:04.600 --> 00:38:06.250
In an Uber.

876
00:38:06.280 --> 00:38:08.250
People's Exhibit 15.

877
00:38:08.280 --> 00:38:10.710
Pick-up time. 12:19 a.m.

878
00:38:10.780 --> 00:38:13.420
Pick-up location.
632 15th Street.

879
00:38:13.520 --> 00:38:15.860
Destination.
77 Greenwich Street.

880
00:38:15.920 --> 00:38:17.290
Is this information accurate?

881
00:38:17.360 --> 00:38:18.460
Yes.

882
00:38:27.890 --> 00:38:29.740
A few years back.

883
00:38:29.770 --> 00:38:33.110
you were arrested for assault. correct?

884
00:38:33.210 --> 00:38:34.470
Yes.

885
00:38:34.570 --> 00:38:37.640
And you have expressed
deep regret

886
00:38:37.740 --> 00:38:39.610
over this incident. correct?

887
00:38:39.710 --> 00:38:41.150
Yes.

888
00:38:41.280 --> 00:38:44.020
You wish it had
never even happened?

889
00:38:44.080 --> 00:38:45.640
Yes. but it did.

890
00:38:45.740 --> 00:38:48.350
and I've gotta live with that.

891
00:38:48.420 --> 00:38:50.990
I imagine
that would be difficult.

892
00:38:51.060 --> 00:38:52.620
It is.

893
00:38:53.810 --> 00:38:57.800
A man should never do
something like that.

894
00:38:57.900 --> 00:39:00.630
no matter what
the circumstances.

895
00:39:05.070 --> 00:39:06.470
Right.

896
00:39:06.570 --> 00:39:10.140
No matter what
the circumstances.

897
00:39:20.320 --> 00:39:22.220
And. uh...

898
00:39:25.360 --> 00:39:27.590
Despite all this.
you continue

899
00:39:27.660 --> 00:39:29.730
to love Angela Cole.

900
00:39:38.270 --> 00:39:40.570
Yes. very much.

901
00:39:48.480 --> 00:39:50.350
Nothing further.

902
00:40:05.530 --> 00:40:07.570
I heard about the mistrial.

903
00:40:08.730 --> 00:40:10.850
Judge pushed them
to reach a verdict.

904
00:40:10.890 --> 00:40:13.660
You pulled up short
on this one. Nolan.

905
00:40:16.310 --> 00:40:18.180
Letting the jury know
what really happened

906
00:40:18.210 --> 00:40:21.580
that day might have made
a difference.

907
00:40:21.710 --> 00:40:24.920
You don't get paid
to do the comfortable thing

908
00:40:25.050 --> 00:40:27.410
or the noble thing.

909
00:40:27.510 --> 00:40:29.390
You get paid to win.
